## Verification Plan

| # | Test | Target | Method |
|---|------|--------|--------|
| 1 | Language Detection Accuracy | >90% (est. current: ~65%) | 200+ messages, 40/register |
| 2 | Intent Classification Accuracy | >85% (est. current: ~70%) | 100 messages with context |
| 3 | E2E Conversation Quality | Avg >4.0/5.0 | 10 convos × 5 registers = 50 total |
| 4 | Regression | All existing tests pass | `test_rag.py`, `scripts/test_full_flow.py` |
| 5 | A/B Test | Higher completion rate | Phase 1+2 to 10% of users |
| 6 | Latency | <3s per response | After adding conversation history |
| 7 | API Cost | <15% increase | Monitor OpenAI dashboard |

---

## Key Decisions

- ✅ **Quick wins first** — Phases 1-2 ship first, fix ~70% of issues with code-only changes
- ✅ **No translation layer** — Continue using native LLM multilingual capability (preserves natural register)
- ✅ **Stay on GPT-5-mini** — Budget-conscious. Consider GPT-4o only if Phase 2 doesn't hit accuracy targets
- ✅ **~15% cost increase acceptable** — From conversation history addition
- ✅ **Tanglish as first-class register** — Throughout entire stack, not just Python bot
- ✅ **Moderate budget** — Fast-classify expansion keeps LLM calls down

## Future Considerations (Out of Scope for Now)

1. **WhatsApp Interactive Messages** — Button/list messages for language, job, country selection bypass NLP entirely. Implement after Phase 3.
2. **Voice Message Optimization** — Whisper language hints + post-transcription normalization for Sinhala/Tamil voice notes.
3. **Analytics Dashboard** — Track per-language metrics, drop-off points, misclassification rates for ongoing improvement.